<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-670-106  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 670 106.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  July 23 1990 v7 n29 p38(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Canadian firm to ship multilingual software. ( Les TechnologiesDiligence Inc.) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Morrissey, Jane.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>The Montreal, CN-based Les Technologies Diligence Inc division ofComterm Inc introduces a number of multilingual local area network(LAN) programs to the US market.andP;  Users have access to French,Spanish, German and English versions at the touch of a key.andP;  LesTechnologies' $895 Network Task Manager (NTM) includes DOS menuingsoftware, a DOS directory manager and software for customizing LANinterfaces.andP;  Because NTM automatically installs different languagelibraries, users can work with different languages from a singleapplication.andP;  The $395 Multi Language Support module adds theability to communicate in French, Spanish and English tothird-party menuing programs.andP;  The $695 Network Postman, anelectronic mail system, includes an integrated word processor.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Comterm Inc. Les Technologies Diligence Inc. (productintroduction).andO;Product:   Network Task Manager (Network management software) (productintroduction)Multi Language Support (Foreign language translation software)(product introduction)Network Postman (Electronic mail system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionForeign LanguagesSoftware packagesAdd-In-On SoftwareNetwork Management SoftwareElectronic Mail Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Jane MorrisseyandM;A Canadian software developer plans to bring to the U.S.andP;  market this summerits suite of multilingual LAN enhancement software, including a menuingpackage for DOS networks.andM;Les Technologies Diligence Inc., a division of Comterm Inc., offers networkmenuing, management and mail programs in languages including English, French,Spanish and German at the touch of a key, company officials said.andM;Compatible with Novell Inc.andP;  NetWare and Banyan Systems Inc.andP;  VINES networks,the packages will be distributed by several major U.S.andP;  resellers within thenext 90 days, the officials said.andM;The firm's flagship product, the $895 Network Task Manager (NTM), is acompilation of DOS menuing software, a DOS directory manager andnetwork-management software for customizing LAN interfaces.andM;Unlike products that offer separate packages for each language, NTMautomatically installs different language libraries so users can work withmultiple languages from a single application, officials said.andM;&quot;The strengths of the system, apart from being bilingual, are its centraladministration .andP;  .  .  and the shell completely unloads from memory uponselecting an item,&quot; said Brian Bird, systems integration manager for EpsonCanada Ltd. in Ottawa, Ontario.andP;  &quot;Users can also modify their own menus, andthe software structures the file server, such as creating a directory called'users' and a subdirectory called 'applications,' which adds consistencyacross the network.&quot;andM;A separate $395 module called Multi Language Support can be added tothird-party menuing packages to allow communication in English, French andSpanish, officials said.andM;The company also offers a $695 electronic-mail system, called NetworkPostman, that features an integrated word processor and the ability to attachup to 10 documents per message and create up to 100 distribution lists.andP;  Acommand-line utility is included for sending short messages and singledocuments from DOS.andM;The Directory Management System -- which is bundled with NTM but also isavailable separately for $85 -- displays directories and files in a treelikefashion and sorts contents by extension, size or date and time.andM;Les Technologies Diligence can be contacted in Montreal at (514) 694-4332.andO;</TEXT></DOC>